definition.value: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of 4-iodo-L-phenylalanine and 4-iodo-D-phenylalanine.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group of rubrofusarin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of piperazines that is piperazine in which the pro-S hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 have each been replaced by a p-hydroxybenzyl group.

An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 8,9-dihydro-4H-phenaleno[1,2-b]furan substituted by methyl groups at positions 1,8,8 and 9R, hydroxy groups at positions 3,4 and 7, methoxy group at position 5 and oxo group at position 6. It is isolated from the soil fungus, Penicillium herquei.

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and  N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3), (1->4) and (1->6), to the galactosamine residue of which is also linked (1->3) a beta-D-galactosyl residue.
beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-D-Glcp6S in which the anomeric configuration of the glucose residue is beta.
A phenolate anion obtained by deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group of rubrofusarin B. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A mixture containing lopinavir and ritonavir. It is a prescription medicine that is used with other antiretroviral medicines to treat Human Immunodeficiency Virus-1 (HIV-1) infection in adults and children 14 days of age and older.
A dipeptide zwitterion consisting of a glycine attached to a dehydrophenylalanine. Major structure at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion that is the alpha,beta-didehydro derivative of phenylalanine. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A beta-D-glucoside resulting from the formal condensation of 1-hydroxy group of beta-D-glucopyranose with the carboxy group of indole-3-butyric acid.
A member of the class of indoles that is 1H-indole substituted by a (1-hydroxy-7,8-dihydro-6H-pyrrolo[1,2-a]pyrazin-5-ium-3-yl)methyl group at position 3. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
A branched-chain saturated fatty acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (S)-2-methylbutanoic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.
A 4alpha-hydroxymethyl steroid that is 5-alpha-cholest-7-en-3beta-ol in which the alpha-hydrogen at position 4 has been replaced by a hydroxymethyl group.
